---
layout: 'base.njk'
---

<article class="wrapper article">
    <header class="article-header">
        <div class="article-header__inner">
            <h1 class="article__title">{{title}}</h1>
            <p class="article__published">Published {{page.date | postDate}}</p>
            {% if description %}<p class="article__description">{{description}}</p>{% endif %}
        </div>
    </header>
    {% if hero %}
    <div class="article__hero popout">
        <img src="{{hero}}" alt="" class="hero-img" loading="eager" eleventy:widths="300, 600, 800, 1200" width="800"
            height="450" sizes="(min-width: 60em) 800px, (min-width: 48em) calc(100vw - 80px), calc(100vw - 48px)">
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="article__content content">
        {% if 'a11ytips' in tags %}
        <section class="article__summary" aria-label="Quick summary">
            <hr>
            a11y tips is a series of short articles (300ish words) which stem from answers to questions I have been
            asked about
            web accessibility. These tips will hopefully help others and may also bring to the surface some obscure
            rules,
            tips and techniques.
            <hr>
        </section>
        {% endif %}
        {{ content | safe}}
    </div>
    <div class="article__footer content">
        <hr>
        <p>Have I missed something important in this article or said something that is wrong? Please message me and let
            me know.</p>
    </div>
</article>